      "sample_id": null,
      "microstructure_uuid": null,
      "technique": "Room temperature compression test",
      "purpose": "Measure yield strength, ductility and work hardening rate of Fe-Al alloys",
      "key_findings": "Work hardening rate shows a sharp peak at 26~30at.%Al, yield strength increases up to 25at.%Al then decreases, ductility has a small peak at ~28at.%Al"
    },
    {
      "characterization_id": "char_02",
      "sample_id": null,
      "microstructure_uuid": null,
      "technique": "Transmission Electron Microscopy (TEM, bright field, weak beam, dark field mode)",
      "purpose": "Observe dislocation structure evolution with Al content",
      "key_findings": "Transition from single dislocations in low Al alloys to superdislocations in high Al ordered alloys, large number of superdislocation dipoles and sessile <100> dislocations in alloys near work hardening peak"
    }
  ],
  "computational_details": [],
  "unmapped_findings": [
    "加工硬化率峰值对应弹性各向异性峰值，认为是25~30at.%Al合金较强的Peierls力使位错优先沿螺型取向，促进偶极子形成，而非弹性各向异性直接导致",
    "未观察到APB管结构，不支持APB管加工硬化模型",
    "28~30at.%Al合金中<111>超位错反应生成的<100>刃型不动位错是额外的加工硬化贡献源",
    "添加0.1at.%B仅小幅提高流动应力，对加工硬化率无显著影响",
    "25at.%Al合金APB能量较低，超位错完全解离为单根位错拖曳APB，无四分量DO3超位错存在"
  ]
}